# Flint — Audio Pipeline

> **WARNING:** Never let AI generate audio pipeline or Tauri IPC code without reviewing every line. These are the two areas where AI-generated code fails silently and is hardest to debug.

## Audio Format
- All audio processed at **16kHz PCM mono** (Whisper's required input format).
- System audio (loopback) and microphone captured as **separate channels**.
- Each channel gets independent RNNoise + VAD before being tagged and merged.
- Tag: `source = "System"` (loopback = interviewer) or `source = "Microphone"` (user).

## RNNoise Configuration
| Parameter | Value |
|---|---|
| Frame size | 480 samples (10ms at 48kHz → downsampled to 16kHz) |
| Latency | < 5ms per frame |

## VAD Configuration (WebRTC VAD)
| Parameter | Value | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Mode | 3 (most aggressive) | Filters most background noise |
| Frame size | 20ms | WebRTC VAD standard |
| Sample rate | 16kHz | Whisper's required input |
| Minimum speech duration | 200ms | Below this = noise artefact |
| Maximum silence gap | 600ms | Triggers end-of-chunk |
| Energy floor | -60 dBFS | Below this = definitely silence |
| Silence threshold | -35 dBFS | Below this = silence |

Silence frames are **NEVER** sent to Whisper.

## Whisper.cpp Configuration
| Parameter | Value | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| `beam_size` | 5 | Default, good quality/speed tradeoff |
| `temperature` | 0.0 | Deterministic, prevents hallucination |
| `language` | `"en"` | Locked — auto-detect adds 200–400ms latency |
| `no_speech_threshold` | 0.6 | Above this = silence |
| `compression_ratio_threshold` | 2.4 | Above this = repetitive hallucination, discard |
| `logprob_threshold` | -1.0 | Below this = low-confidence, discard |
| `word_timestamps` | `true` | Per-word timing for speaker-turn heuristics |
| `initial_prompt` | `"Professional interview conversation."` | Improves accuracy on formal language |
| `max_context` | -1 | No context carry-over between chunks |

## Ring Buffer Rules
- **16KB ring buffer per channel.** Never flush to disk.
- Audio cleared on session end. Zero bytes of audio on disk — hard requirement.
- On audio stream drop: cpal detects error → reinitialise within 5 seconds.
- Transcript panel inserts `[audio gap - Ns missing]` marker on drop.

## Channel Mixing
- Sum to mono **after** per-channel VAD, **before** Whisper.
- Chunk delivery: on VAD end-of-speech signal, max 1 second.

## System Audio Loopback per Platform
- **Linux (PipeWire):** loopback module loaded automatically if not present.
- **Linux (PulseAudio):** `pactl load-module module-loopback` at session start.
- **Linux (ALSA only):** warn user — loopback requires additional setup.
- **Windows:** WASAPI loopback capture.
- **macOS:** BlackHole virtual audio driver.
  - If system audio loopback fails at health check: guide user through BlackHole install + Audio MIDI Setup multi-output device creation.
  - If user skips: session proceeds but only mic captured — persistent amber warning: *"System audio not configured. Flint will only hear your voice."*
- **X11 Linux:** show hard warning, block `READY → LIVE` transition.
